Dialogs.Dialog: Okay. Rinko was just in the mood.
I see. Good. So, where shall we go？
I'd love to go, but... Rinko has to go home early.
No good... Well, I guess we'll go home without detours.
Well, I guess it's settled then.
There, huh... If you want to go there, I have no choice.
Rinko has no time to stop by. Can't we just go home together？
I see. Well, let's go straight home.
Okay. You want to go there？
Hmm... I like it there. I don't mind it.
Why would I do that, there's no way I'm going... See you.
Hey... do you want to stop by somewhere on our way back home？
Yay. Where do you want to go？
Bummer. Well, how about if we just go home together？
(Oh no... It's past the meeting time...)
You're late... I'm here to pick you up, you should thank me.
This is bad！ It's past the meeting time...
I'm still here. You're disqualified for having you girlfriend pick you up.
Ah！ It's past the meeting time...
Ah... my ass. I've come to pick you up.
It can't be... did you really forget our promise, ▲主人公＊▲？
Ah, I was just about to go, ▲小早川＊▲.
I came to see your panicked face, ▲主人公＊▲.
I came to your classroom. How about it, your girlfriend is coming to pick you up？
Thank you. I'll be right out.
Sorry, did you wait long, ▲小早川＊▲？
"Sorry, did you wait long？" he says. Ah, so lovey-dovey.
Shut it, you！ Don't go around saying unnecessary things, okay？
Hah, your friend seems to be doing fine.
Sorry to keep you waiting, ▲小早川＊▲.
Yo, you two. You guys getting off to school together？ That's hot！
Your friend uses very retro expressions... Well, he's funny.
Sorry, did you wait for me ▲小早川＊▲！？
Hey, Kobayakawa. You should be that nice to us, too.
What are you talking about？ You're an idiot.
(I see that you can talk normally with the boys in your class now, ▲小早川＊▲.)
You guys. What are you doing here？
I'm just asking about the Library Committee, is that a problem？
Oh, okay. Be sure to do your work as a committee member.
You guys are socializing like high schoolers, right？
I don't know what it is about socializing that is so unlike high school students. Could you please tell me？
Ah, well no... Okay, that's fine.
I think that's Kobayakawa. The other is a 2nd year...
Ah... Emm, I'm his senior member of the Library Committee.
Yes. I was consulting with my senior about how to run the library. Excuse me.
Go and get it. I'll be waiting for you here.
That's fine. If you don't have a textbook, it's a good reason why you could not do your homework.
Ah！ I forgot something in the classroom...
You want to go back for it？
Hmm, nah. It's not a big deal.
I forgot the handouts that were handed out today... Can you follow me to class？
Yeah, I rarely get to go to first-year classes, so I'm kind of looking forward to it.
Oh wait... Found it. It was sandwiched between my Japanese notebook.
Hey, is that your 2nd grade homeroom teacher over there？
Ah, yes she is... Is that the freshman you're with？
The girl in the next class... suspicious...
Oh... that couple, they are both classmates in Rinko's class.
You're always nagging Rinko to obey the school rules, but you're having a great time doing it yourself.
Well, at least we're going out.
What？ ...You got a girl on your mind？
No, she's just a girl from my class――
Ah, someone came... it's a boy from my class！ I see, an older girlfriend and a younger boyfriend, huh.
Why are you... Oh, that girl is putting something in the shoe box...
Yeah, don't you think they are love letters？ It would be tactless to interrupt.
What are you... Oh, is that a... confession？
Maybe, but peeking is in poor taste. We better go quickly.
Why are you so nervous, ▲小早川＊▲？
Hmm... I've been told that my classmate is going to confess their feelings to their senior today.
So you're nervous all the way down. Reminds you of our own time, doesn't it, ▲小早川＊▲？
That's good. Come on, let's go.
(Ah, you're talking with someone. Seems weird, ▲小早川＊▲...)
Were you here？ Let's go, ▲主人公＊▲.
Yeah, something just asked for my name and contact information. I ignored it.
Were you talking to someone just now or something, ▲小早川＊▲？
He said he was in the third grade. "What's your class and name？" He asked.
No way. I scared him by kicking him, and then he disappeared.
You're late. Rinko had a hard time, ▲主人公＊▲.
I was picked up by a boy I didn't know.
There's nothing going on. If you're so worried, don't leave Rinko alone.
Sorry to keep you waiting, ▲小早川＊▲.
Ah... Hah, I wish you could have been slower.
A cat wandered in and I was playing with it. It ran away when it heard your voice.
Ah... don't suddenly call me out loud. It run away.
A beautiful calico cat. We should go for a walk...
My bad. But you have an appointment with me.
Yes, the girl who often breaks into the school. It's like she's coming to see Rinko, she's so cute.
Heh, I wish I could have seen her.
I found a pen case on the floor...
Does it have a written name？
Even high school students don't write their names on their belongings.
I see... Then I'll stop by the staff room and deliver it.
I found some stationery. And it has a sticker of Rinko's favorite band on it.
Heh, it looks like you put it up yourself.
I feel the love. I wonder who could have dropped it off.
If we find out, maybe you will have the same hobbies.
I found a cosmetic pouch. If I deliver it to the teacher's office, I'm afraid the owner will get in trouble with the teacher.
I see... So, shall we put it back where it belongs？
Ah, so it was the teacher's.
Yeah. You picked it up for me？ Thanks.
What a surprise, it was the teacher's... Well, I'm glad you found the owner safely.
Eh？ Oh, sorry, I was listening to music.
Hey, what are you doing？ If you're looking for Rinko, I'm over here.
Ah！ Haha, looks like I got the wrong person, ▲小早川＊▲.
I don't know if you're looking at the wrong girlfriend, or if you're just being rude.
How did you know that Rinko was behind you ▲主人公＊▲？
Wow, that's great. Is that the power of love？
Oh, there's the life guidance teacher.
It's a bad idea to be found...
Rumor has it that they make you write 20 pages of reflection essays. You're not gonna read it anyway.
Let's change paths to avoid getting into trouble.
Yo. You got a date after school？ I'm jealous！
Is dating your girlfriend after school something to be proud of？
I'm proud of my girlfriend, not of dating her.
Lately my dad has been nagging me to come home early.
That's probably part of it, but... he wants Rinko to take care of his little brother. I'm sure he'd like to have some time alone with mom.
She says "Go buy toilet paper." I'm a maiden on a date and she asks me to buy toilet paper...
Hello？ Yes, having fun？ ...Yes, I understand... chocolate？ Okay, be a good boy then.
Little brother. He called me on my mom's cell phone. He asked for a souvenir.
You don't have to look for her. Come on, let's go.
Hmm, an e-mail. Sorry, wait a minute.
It's a mail order site. It says, "The item you are looking for is now in stock." What should I do？
Online shopping, huh. Seems like you are making good use of it, ▲小早川＊▲.
Hello？ ...No... Yes, I'm sure... Yes, excuse me.
You're more polite than when I call you...
That's right. In your case, there is no problem even at the lowest response level.
Muscle cramps？ Have you been exercising？
Maybe Rinko is too old for house cleaning... Not as old as you though.
Just one year above, you know.
Can we stop by the convenience store later？
Souvenir for my brother. He's been collecting the freebies that come with the snacks.
Ah, right. Let me know if you find a hundred-yen store on the way.
I was shocked to hear the other day that something I bought for 300 yen is also sold at the 100-yen store. I won't admit it until I see for myself.
Well, I don't know how you feel.
...Wait, wasn't Rinko on cleaning duty today？
What？ I'm not sure why you're asking me that...
Hmmm, no, it should have been next week. Yeah, right？
I told you I don't know.
We meet in an unusual place, don't we？
Really. Anyway, just saying hello, senpai. I don't want to bother you, so I'll be going.
(Somehow... The friends of my girlfriend make me nervous.)
Look. Isn't she cute in that dress she's wearing？
Hmm. I'd say it's cute, but...
Would Rinko look good in it？
(That's a middle schooler. I better shut up.)
I'm kind of craving a cup of ramen.
No！ I'll hold off until I get home. I'll bear with it for the time being, so from now on, no talking about cup ramen.
There's a new cafe near the school.
I see, do you want to go？
No, because there's going to be a lot of students. We'd have to be a very assertive couple.
That's it for today... It's going to be a long night until tomorrow.
Call me if you get lonely.
Good job today. See you tomorrow.
We part ways here, see you.
Tomorrow is my day off. I'm sorry, that doesn't mean we can't spend a lot of time together.
Well, tomorrow is my day off. I'll stay up late.
Tomorrow is my day off, so I think I'll take it easy. See you later.
